            <gmd:supplementalInformation>
                <gco:CharacterString>******************************************* Data files are ready to be opened by Tecplot (a visualization tool for fluid dynamics). Visual illustrations of this dataset are provided in the folder "plot". ***************************************************** * Physical parameters for the large-eddy simulation * ***************************************************** Domain size of the LES: 1000m x 1000m x 150m Initial mixed layer depth: z_i = 100 m Wind direction: x-direction Wind friction velocity: u* = 0.0125 m/s Wave propagation direction: x-direction Sea water density: 1031.0 kg/m^3 Sea water viscosity: 1.08E-3 kg/(m s) Oil releasing rate: 1 kg/s Oil releasing depth: z = -150 m Oil density: 859.9 kg/m^3 Oil droplet diameters: d = 88, 125, 177, 250, and 354 microns ************************ * For case La_t = 0.36 * ************************ Wavelength: 120 m Wave amplitude: 1.6 m Stokes drift velocity: Us = 0.096 m/s Turbulent Langmuir number: La_t = sqrt(u*/Us) = 0.36 ************************ * For case La_t = 0.43 * ************************ Wavelength: 60 m Wave amplitude: 0.8 m Stokes drift velocity: Us = 0.068 m/s Turbulent Langmuir number: La_t = sqrt(u*/Us) = 0.43 ************************ * For case La_t = 0.51 * ************************ Wavelength: 30 m Wave amplitude: 0.4 m Stokes drift velocity: Us = 0.048 m/s Turbulent Langmuir number: La_t = sqrt(u*/Us) = 0.51 ************************ * For case La_t = 0.61 * ************************ Wavelength: 15 m Wave amplitude: 0.2 m Stokes drift velocity: Us = 0.034 m/s Turbulent Langmuir number: La_t = sqrt(u*/Us) = 0.61 *********************************************************************** In Vertical_eddy_diffusivity.dat *********************************************************************** Definition of variables: z_normalized_by_zm: vertial coordinate "z" normalized by initial mixed layer depth "zi" Kcz_normalized_by_ustar_zi: vertical eddy diffusivity "Kcz" normalized by wind friction velocity "u*" and initial mixed layer depth "zi" The dataset includes four different La_t flow conditions. For each flow condition, results for five different oil droplet diameters are included. The ID of each case is indicated in the "zone" names in the data file.||||</gco:CharacterString>
